Technology: Maven Archetype - Basic
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

  Maven Arvchetypes are used to create a basic structure for a certain kind of project. A simple 
  example is the archetype that creates the structure for Maven site. These archetypes can be 
  easily adapted for individual use and different types of projects (e.g. a webappliciation).

  This document first introduces an archetype based on the BPSE Basic Sample that creates a 
  project which can be compiled directly after creation and contains a very simple program to
  show software concepts. After this the document shows how archetypes themselfs are designed and
  can be created for individual use.

* Archetype Usage
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

** Download & Installation
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

  You can download the archetype from this {{{bpse-archetype-basic-0.1.0.jar}link}}.

  To use this archetype you have to install it first into your Maven Repository.

      * Open a console window and change to the directory <<<${basedir}/bpse-archetype-basic>>>.

      * Run <<<mvn install>>>.

** Archetype Usage
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  
  To create a project with your specific namespace and project name type and run the following 
  into a console window from a desired directory.

+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
  mvn archetype:create \
	-DarchetypeGroupId=at.ac.tuwien.ifs.qse \
	-DarchetypeArtifactId=bpse-archetype-basic \
	-DarchetypeVersion=0.1.0 \
	-DgroupId=my.groupId \
	-DartifactId=my-artifactId
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+

  Where <<<my.groupId>>> is the namespace and <<<my-artifactId>>> is the name of your project.

